Mr Webb Could you please tell us a little bit about the sports program here at Forest Lake.

00:03:17.990 --> 00:03:32.000
Yes I'd love to tell you about the sports program. Here at Forest Lake we offer a variety of different sports to cater for all the different children that attend our school. So we try to make sure that everyone at our school's catered for for all the different sports that are offered from the Greater Brisbane area.

00:03:34.210 --> 00:03:49.090
The school was built specifically as two schools within a big school. The community were very very concerned about their students getting lost in a large school, so we've got a designated junior secondary school.

00:03:49.180 --> 00:03:56.360
In our school the teachers come to the students, so the students tend to be in a home classroom when they are in Year 8.

00:03:57.300 --> 00:04:01.970
So Mr Culverhouse, key question - What is the PRIDE Program?

00:04:02.060 --> 00:04:12.780
The PRIDE Program's put in place for behaviour and recognition in our school. It's about rewarding kids for the good things they do. And correcting them when they do things wrong.

00:04:12.830 --> 00:04:25.930
We provide students with daily rewards with a sticker process where they get a sticker for doing the right thing in the classroom or in the playgroud and that way they can build up a bank of those stickers and trade them in for positive rewards and items.

00:04:27.750 --> 00:04:30.800
[Off camera] The staff really care about our students. 

00:04:31.600 --> 00:04:35.980
I think the relationship staff form with the students is incredibly special.

00:04:36.160 --> 00:04:45.230
The students really do appreciate what we do for them because you'll see the past students come back to say hello. They want to keep the bonds going and keep the friendships and connnections.

00:04:45.330 --> 00:04:47.020
[Off camera] When they see you when you're out in the shops...

00:04:47.070 --> 00:04:51.740
YES!! They'll run right across the shopping centre to say hello!

